    <my:Date>2015-05-15</my:Date>
    <my:Title>Deck or Hold Washing</my:Title>
  </my:Details>
  <my:Hazards>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="1">
      <my:Description>Water - jet</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>2</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>4</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Water jet should never be directed at another person; 
b) Pressure in the hose should be adjusted according to working space/area; 
c) Hose should not be left unattended when water running.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="2">
      <my:Description>Debris - cargo residue / paint flakes / rust particles</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>2</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>4</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Reduce the pressure of water jet; 
b) Crew to stay away from splashing mixture of water and cargo.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="3">
      <my:Description>Electricity</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Water jet should never be directed at electric installation; 
b) Portable lightning equipment and its cables should not be submerged in the water; 
c) Where possible electric equipment should be isolated.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="4">
      <my:Description>Electronic Equipment</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>2</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>4</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Crew to be instructed regarding positions of vulnerable equipment; 
b) Water jet should not be directed at such a equipment to prevent unintentional activation (e.g. EPIRB) or damage.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="5">
      <my:Description>Chemicals - skin irritation / chemical burns</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>2</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>4</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Consult manufacturer’s instruction/relevant Material Safety Data Sheet regarding health precautions when using cleaning agents; 
b) Consult ‘Dealing With Hazardous Substances’ Risk Assessment; 
c) Consult Material Safety Data Sheet regarding cargo reaction when in contact with water or other substances.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="6">
      <my:Description>Gas - hazardous vapours</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Consult Material Safety Data Sheet regarding cargo reaction when in contact with water or other substances; 
b) Consult relevant sections of IMDG Code, if applicable.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
  </my:Hazards>
